\
English Translation: Amla (Indian Gooseberry) is beneficial in all seasons. Amla\
is also called 'Amalakam'. For maintaining the health of the body, the use of\
this fruit must be done. This fruit is very useful for increasing the light of\
the eyes, for increasing the beauty of hair, and for increasing the glow of the\
skin. Generally, it is used in the form of jam (avaleha) or pickle. It is also\
helpful in the formation of red blood cells. By consuming this, anemia does not\
occur in the body. In the summer season, this fruit removes the heat of the\
body. By its regular consumption, memory power also increases.\
\
